26/01/2009
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- The newest party in the country, the New Serb Democracy (NOVA), came into existence on Saturday (January 24th) in a move to consolidate all Serb political structures in the country. 
Its leader, former Serb People's Party leader Andrija Mandic, announced at its founding congress that it plans to take part in the March parliamentary and local elections, in a coalition with other opposition parties. 
The Movement for Change and the Socialist People's Party say they are on board. 
(Tanjug, B92 - 25/01/09; RTCG - 24/01/09)
